    <h2 id="causes-of-bloating">What Causes Bloating and How Gummies Can Help</h2>

    <p>Bloating is the subjective sensation of abdominal fullness, tightness, or distension caused by excess gas production, impaired gut motility, or fluid retention. It affects an estimated 16 to 31% of the general population and is the most commonly reported gastrointestinal symptom in clinical practice. While occasional bloating after large meals is normal, chronic bloating that occurs daily or interferes with quality of life warrants investigation into root causes — and targeted supplementation.</p>

