      <p class="key-stat-txt">Of adults report regular bloating, making it the <strong>most common digestive complaint</strong> in the United States. Women are affected at nearly twice the rate of men, partly due to hormonal influences on gut motility and fluid retention.</p>
    </div>

    <p>The key to effective bloating supplementation is matching the ingredient to the cause. Digestive enzyme deficiency leads to incomplete food breakdown, producing gas as gut bacteria ferment undigested carbohydrates, fats, and proteins. Gut microbiome imbalance (dysbiosis) produces excess gas through bacterial fermentation patterns that favor gas-producing species. Food intolerances trigger inflammation and fluid retention in the gut lining. Each of these causes responds to different ingredients — which is why a comprehensive bloating gummy should ideally address multiple mechanisms.</p>

    <div class="info-cards">
