    <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions About Bloating Gummies</h2>
    <details class="fq"><summary>What causes bloating?</summary><p>Excess gas from fermentable carbohydrates, food intolerances, inadequate enzyme production, gut dysbiosis, eating too quickly, and hormonal fluctuations. Chronic bloating affects 16-31% of adults.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Do bloating gummies actually work?</summary><p>Effectiveness depends on matching the ingredient to the cause. Digestive enzymes help with food-related bloating. Probiotics address microbiome imbalance. Herbal carminatives reduce gas. A 2011 study found multi-enzyme supplements significantly reduced bloating and gas after meals.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>How quickly do bloating gummies work?</summary><p>Enzymes: 30-60 minutes with meals. Herbal carminatives: 1-2 hours. Probiotics: 2-4 weeks of consistent use for microbiome shifts.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Should I take probiotics or digestive enzymes?</summary><p>Enzymes for meal-triggered bloating from specific foods. Probiotics for chronic bloating with irregular bowel habits. Combination products provide the broadest coverage if unsure.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Can bloating gummies help with water retention?</summary><p>Products with dandelion root, potassium, or magnesium can reduce water retention. Most bloating gummies target gas-related bloating instead. Love Wellness Bye Bye Bloat specifically addresses hormonal water retention.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Are bloating gummies safe daily?</summary><p>Yes. Enzymes, probiotics, ginger, peppermint, and fennel are safe for daily use. If chronic bloating persists after 4 weeks, consult a gastroenterologist.</p></details>

